claim: Flublok (quadrivalent) was evaluated in the pivotal trial against Fluarix (quadrivalent standard-dose vaccine).
explanation: A table titled ‘Adults 18–49 Years of Age, Study 1’ showing case definitions (positive culture with matched strains, any ILI, etc.), with columns for Flublok (N=2344) and saline placebo (N=2304) listing number of cases, rates (%), calculated vaccine efficacy (%) and 95% confidence intervals. The table compares Flublok with saline placebo and does not include any comparison to Fluarix quadrivalent, so it does not support the claim. Note: The visible portion of the figure clearly shows only a saline placebo comparator; no mention of Fluarix is present.
